Gov. Gboyega Oyetola, of Osun, has approved the appointment of chairmen and members of Rent Tribunals, for the nine Federal Constituencies in the state.  Oyetola, in a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Ismail Omipidan, on Monday, in Osogbo, said the appointment was in accordance with the Residential Accommodation (Rent Control) Law Cap. 144 Laws of Osun, 2002, Section 5(1)(a) and (b). The governor said that the constitution of the rent tribunals was aimed at enhancing communal peace and dispensation of justice, in landlord/tenant related disputes. Oyetola said that through the rent tribunals, peaceful and amicable resolution of rent related issues would be guaranteed in all the federal constituencies. The governor said the appointment takes immediate effect.